      {
        "content": "SWC-116: Block values as a proxy for time\n\nContracts often use block.timestamp / block.number for time-dependent logic. Miners/validators can manipulate block.timestamp within a small window, and block times vary. Remediation: avoid block values for randomness; tolerate the manipulation window for deadlines only where economically safe.",
        "doc_id": "SWC-116",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
